remainder showed some differences in this pattern, such as non-L3 morphology (3 
cases), absence of CD20 (3 cases), CD10+ (4 cases), TdT+ (3 cases), c mu+ (1 
case), lack of surface light chains (1 case). This rare ALL subset seems to be 
characterized by a high phenotype heterogeneity, indicating various degrees of 
differentiation.

